The paper deals with the tradeoff between storage and download cost in private information retrieval systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the security aspect of private information retrieval (cs.CR) and the coding techniques used to achieve capacity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper suggests the need for more sophisticated bounding techniques, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
